						               													<description>In this very simple and fun game, the players take turns trying to get all the ingredients to make a nice fruit salad: grapes, blueberries, strawberries, kiwis, tangerines and bananas. The first one to complete the set wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In terms of gameplay, initially there's a pile with fruit and &amp;quot;veggie&amp;quot; tokens. Each player on their turn rolls two custom dice, one with the 6 fruits on its faces and one blank, except for one face, that shows a broccoli (&amp;quot;veggie&amp;quot;). Depending on the roll, they either pick up a corresponding fruit token or a veggie token from the pile. If they already have the fruit, they have the option of picking up a second one (only up to two per fruit are allowed) or return their fruit token back to the pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Veggie tokens are &amp;quot;jokers&amp;quot;, in that they can stand in the place of any fruit token. However if you roll for veggie and already have one, you have to give it back; you can have at most one veggie at any given time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winning condition is having exactly 6 different tokens (6 fruit or 5 fruit and a veggie) with no duplicates.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
